vs:contributing-factor.vs:name: Consumer Default Information
vs:contributing-factor.vs:description: The existence of consumer default information can be a powerful indicator of risk.

vs:contributing-factor.vs:name: Historical Consumer Credit Application Information
vs:contributing-factor.vs:description: The type and frequency of historical credit applications can be an indicator of risk.

vs:contributing-factor.vs:name: Public Adverse Information
vs:contributing-factor.vs:description: The existence of public adverse information such as court judgements and writs can have a powerful impact on risk.

vs:contributing-factor.vs:name: Consumer Credit Application Pattern
vs:contributing-factor.vs:description: The type and frequency of credit applications can impact risk. Research shows that applicants with a higher risk typically apply for credit more often.

vs:contributing-factor.vs:name: Default Information Recorded
vs:contributing-factor.vs:description: The existence of default information on the consumer file can be a very powerful indicator of risk.

vs:contributing-factor.vs:name: Individual Shopping Pattern
vs:contributing-factor.vs:description: The type and frequency of credit applications can impact risk. Research shows that applicants with a higher risk typically apply for credit more often.

vs:contributing-factor.vs:name: Default Judgement Information Recorded
vs:contributing-factor.vs:description: The existence of default judgement information on the applicant's file can have a powerful impact on risk.

vs:contributing-factor.vs:name: Specific Default Data
vs:contributing-factor.vs:description: Specific default information has been shown to have an impact on the risk.
